Pioneer has revealed the first UHD Blu-ray rewritable optical drives for desktop PCs. The BDR-S11 J-BK and BDR-S11 J-X Blu-ray drives are set to release in Japan in late February. The devices fit in 5.25-inch desktop drive bays and are able to write to four-layer Blu-ray discs and rewrite three-layer discs. Pioneer listed the following minimum hardware requirements for UHD Blu-ray playback: Users will also need a UHD display with HDR support to play content at the highest level of quality. There is currently no international pricing for Pioneer’s UHD Blu-ray drives.